{
  "word": "association",
  "wordRoot": [
    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#26624\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">association</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(n.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>1530年代，“为了共同目的而聚集在一起的行动”，源自中世纪拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">associationem</span>（主格 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">associatio</span>），动作名词，来自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">associare</span> 的过去分词词干“加入”，来自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">ad</span> 的同化形式“到”（参见 <a href=\"/cn/word/ad-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ad- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">ad-</a>）+ <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">sociare</span> “与...联合”，来自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">socius</span> “伴侣，盟友”（来自 PIE <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">*sokw-yo-</span>，带有后缀的词根 <a href=\"/cn/word/*sekw-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *sekw- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*sekw-</a>（1）“跟随”）。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins><p>“具有共同目的的组织人员”的意义可追溯至1650年代。 “心理联系”的意义可追溯至1680年代； “被其他事物提醒的质量或事物”的意义可追溯至1810年。</p>"
    }
  ],
  "relate": [
    {
      "title": "soccer<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(n.)</div>",
      "html": "<p>1889年， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">socca</i>，后来 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">socker</i>（1891年）， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">soccer</i>（1895年），最初是大学俚语（以滑稽的方式形成 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of -er \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/-er\">-er</a>（3）），源自 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Assoc.</i> 的缩写，即 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of association \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/association\">association</a> 在 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Football Association</i> 中的缩写（与橄榄球相区别）。这是一个不寻常的构词方式，但那些这样做的人可能避免了以 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Assoc</i> 的前三个字母命名。<i class=\"foreign notranslate\">.</i> 与之相比，参见 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">rugger</i>（在 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of rugby \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/rugby\">rugby</a> 下），还有1890年代的英国学生俚语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">leccer</i>，源自 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">lecture</i>（名词）。</p>"
    },
    {
      "title": "ad-<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\"></div>",
      "html": "<p>这个词缀表示方向或附加，源自拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ad</i>，意为“到，朝向”（空间或时间）； 作为前缀时，有时仅仅是强调作用，表示“关于，与...有关”，源自 PIE 词根 <a rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *ad- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/*ad-\">*ad-</a>，意为“到，靠近，于...之间”。</p><p>在 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">sc-</i> 、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\">sp-</i> 和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">st-</i> 之前，简化为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">a-</i>； 在许多辅音前改为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ac-</i>，然后根据后面的辅音重新拼写为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">af-</i> 、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ag-</i> 、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\">al-</i> 等（如 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of affection \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/affection\">affection</a> 、<a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of aggression \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/aggression\">aggression</a>）。还可以参考 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ap- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/ap-\">ap-</a>（1）。</p><p>在古法语中，所有情况下都缩写为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">a-</i>（这种演变在梅洛文吉安拉丁语中已经开始），但法语在14世纪重新塑造了其书写形式，效仿拉丁模式，英语在15世纪也从古法语中学习了这种方式。在许多情况下，发音也随之改变。</p><p>在中世纪末期，法语和英语的过度纠正“恢复”了一些从未有过的单词的 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">-d-</i> 或重复辅音（如 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of accursed \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/accursed\">accursed</a> 、<a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of afford \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/afford\">afford</a>）。在英格兰，这个过程比在法国更进一步（在法国，方言有时会抵制这种学究式的语言），导致了英语中的 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of adjourn \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/adjourn\">adjourn</a> 、<a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of advance \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/advance\">advance</a> 、<a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of address \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/address\">address</a> 、<a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of advertisement \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/advertisement\">advertisement</a>（现代法语为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ajourner</i> 、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\">avancer</i> 、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\">adresser</i> 、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\">avertissement</i>）。在现代的词汇构成中，有时认为 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ad-</i> 和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ab-</i> 是相反的，但这在古典拉丁语中并不是这样。</p>"
    },
    {
      "title": "*sekw-<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(1)</div>",
      "html": "<p>原始印欧语根词，意为“跟随”。</p><p>它构成或部分构成以下单词： <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of associate \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/associate\">associate</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of association \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/association\">association</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of consequence \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/consequence\">consequence</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of consequent \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/consequent\">consequent</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of dissociate \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/dissociate\">dissociate</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ensue \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/ensue\">ensue</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of execute \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/execute\">execute</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of extrinsic \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/extrinsic\">extrinsic</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of intrinsic \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/intrinsic\">intrinsic</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of obsequious \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/obsequious\">obsequious</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of persecute \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/persecute\">persecute</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of persecution \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/persecution\">persecution</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of prosecute \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/prosecute\">prosecute</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of pursue \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/pursue\">pursue</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of second \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/second\">second</a>（形容词）“第二个”； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of second \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/second\">second</a>（名词）“一分钟的六十分之一”； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of sect \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/sect\">sect</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of secundine \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/secundine\">secundine</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of segue \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/segue\">segue</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of sequacious \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/sequacious\">sequacious</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of sequel \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/sequel\">sequel</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of sequence \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/sequence\">sequence</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of sequester \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/sequester\">sequester</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of sociable \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/sociable\">sociable</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of social \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/social\">social</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of society \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/society\">society</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of socio- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/socio-\">socio-</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of subsequent \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/subsequent\">subsequent</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of sue \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/sue\">sue</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of suit \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/suit\">suit</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of suite \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/suite\">suite</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of suitor \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/suitor\">suitor</a>； <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of tocsin \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/tocsin\">tocsin</a>。</p><p>它是假设的源头，其存在的证据由以下单词提供：梵语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">sacate</i> “陪伴，跟随”； 阿维斯塔语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">hacaiti</i>，希腊语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">hepesthai</i> “跟随”； 拉丁语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">sequi</i> “跟随，接着”， <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">secundus</i> “第二，接下来的”； 立陶宛语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">seku, sekti</i> “跟随”； 古爱尔兰语 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">sechim</i> “我跟随”。</p>"
    }
